This paper deals with knowledge representation formalisms and query languages, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the logical underpinnings of the W3C OWL standards, which falls under the category of computational logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions conjunctive queries, which are a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and cryptography (cs.CR).
